  "body": "i noticed that if i try to do `./bin/lodestar init --enr.ip 9.9.9.9` and i check the enr at enr-viewer.com, it does not show the ip.  should we allow the user to be able to make new enr entries via the enr options overwrites whenever those entries aren't already in the enr?  seems like it could be useful, but i'm also not sure what the original rationale was for not allowing this, so i'm open to hearing about that as well.",
