    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "this might also be part of a larger discussion about whether or not we want to allow the user to overwrite an *existing* beacon config (i.e. one that has already been initialized).  when i pass any other cli option to `init` when we already have an existing testnet folder and beacon config, it doesn't overwrite the entry.  maybe this is something we need to talk about supporting in general?  they can always update the beacon config file by hand, sure, but seems like it might be potentially convenient to be able to update it via cli regardless of whether there's an existing beacon config or not.",
